## 4. Final Interpretation

Across all five experiment generations, the clearest pattern is:

- boosting models remain strongest on clean advanced session-level features
- data quality and leakage control matter as much as architecture choice
- Model5 improves the repository by making the tabular result more trustworthy and by adding a full adversarial evaluation layer
- adversarial training substantially recovers robustness for both tabular and temporal models

If the project continues beyond Model5, the next most meaningful improvement is likely to come from more realistic event-level temporal data and stronger real-world threat modeling rather than more architectural complexity alone.
